# ============================================================================
#  .env.example — secret/config bootstrap stub
# ============================================================================
#  ROLE (assists Phase 1–3): a "name catalog" of the environment variables the runtime reads.
#  This file decides nothing — it never sets the real values. It only shows the key names and formats.
#
#  Usage
#  -----
#    cp .env.example .env        # copy, then fill in the real values
#    # .env is excluded from commits via .gitignore — so secrets are never committed.
#
#  No-hardcoding principle
#  ----------------
#  Model/operation-dependent values (API keys, passwords, tokens, external URLs, paths) must not be
#  embedded in source — always inject them via environment variables or a config file. (memory [feedback_no_hardcoding_principle])
#
#  STARTUP MUST VALIDATE
#  ----------------------------------------
#  The application boot code must **fail loudly immediately** when a required key is missing, rather than a "silent None":
#      import os
#      api_key = os.environ["{{PROJECT_PREFIX}}_API_KEY"]   # KeyError aborts immediately if missing
#  Without boot-time validation, it blows up late deep in the runtime via a None reference (a stability-NFR violation).
# ============================================================================

# ── example keys (commented out — replace with real keys) ────────────────────────────────
# {{PROJECT_PREFIX}}_API_KEY=replace-me
# {{PROJECT_PREFIX}}_DB_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/dbname
# {{PROJECT_PREFIX}}_DATA_DIR=/var/lib/{{PROJECT_NAME}}

# ── environment profile ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# {{PROJECT_PREFIX}}_ENV=development          # development | staging | production
# LOG_LEVEL=INFO
